{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/11455", "repo": "rails", "body": "It makes sense to me for this to be defined on the `abstract_adapter`. You may want to restart the build to see if the MySQL adapter errors were flickering.\r\n\r\nSome unsolicited advice though: I'd really recommend using the same database for testing/dev/production. There are significant differences between SQLite and Postgres that can show up even if you are sticking to ORM methods. SQLite will cast strings to integers more readily than Postgres will, for example.", "_id": {"$oid": "5237d41bbd3543c151008043"}, "issue_id": 11455, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/21250224", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/11455#issuecomment-21250224", "updated_at": "2013-07-19T13:48:20Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sorentwo/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sorentwo/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sorentwo/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sorentwo/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/sorentwo", "login": "sorentwo", "gravatar_id": "c4d700e708f2a338a737d0fb80297731", "html_url": "https://github.com/sorentwo", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sorentwo/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sorentwo/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sorentwo/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/c4d700e708f2a338a737d0fb80297731?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fbf1a61ab02e3fa63fdd104e275614748.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sorentwo/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 270831, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sorentwo/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2013-07-19T13:48:20Z", "id": 21250224, "owner": "rails"}
